		<body>
			<!--<p>EHRI-DR-19420806-IT_EN</p>
      <p>Report by <persName ref="#ehri_raimondo_giustiniani">Giustiniani</persName>, <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3186886/zagreb.html">Zagreb</placeName>, to the Italian
          <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005042">Foreign
          Ministry</orgName> dated <date when="1942-08-06">6 August 1942</date>.</p>
      <p>R. Legation of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3175395/italian-republic.html"
          >Italy</placeName></p>
      <p>Cable no. 3680/1010</p>-->
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19420806-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Addressed to R. <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005042">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</orgName>,
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3169070/rome.html">Rome</placeName></p>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3186886/zagreb.html">Zagreb</placeName>, <date when="1942-08-06">6th August 1942</date>, Year
				XX</p>
			<p>Re: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864?dlid=deu" type="subject">The Jews</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3202326/republic-of-croatia.html">Croatia</placeName> – New <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-542" type="subject">measures</term> concerning them.</p>
			<p>Ref. Ministerial Cable no. 8/13948 of <date when="1942-07-29">29th July</date> last.</p>
			<p>While, by arrangement with <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-1338">Supersloda</orgName>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> living in the coastal strip of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3202326/republic-of-croatia.html">Croatia</placeName> are about to be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">transferred</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-614" type="subject">concentrated</term>, several messages from R.
				subordinate Offices – cable no. 432 from R. Consul in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3193935/osijek.html">Osijek</placeName>,
				dated <date when="1942-07-24">24th July</date>, cable from the R.Vice Consulate in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3204541/banja-luka.html">Banja Luka</placeName> of <date when="1942-07-30">30th July</date>, etc.
				– give the impression that this country’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish
					problem</term>, which has repeatedly been the object of drastic <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-542" type="subject">measures</term>, is now entering a new
				stage that might be the conclusive one.</p>
			<p>The new actions for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-618" type="subject">concentrating people</term>
				–approx. 2,000 in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3193935/osijek.html">Osijek</placeName>, approx. 200 in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3204541/banja-luka.html">Banja Luka</placeName> – seem to foreshadow a mass transfer at the disposal
				of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1032" type="subject">German authorities</term> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1181" type="subject">occupied Oriental territories</term>, in accordance
				with a plan of which I have already reported on another occasion.</p>
			<p>As for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3186886/zagreb.html">Zagreb</placeName>, a poster put up in the streets on <date
					when="1942-07-27">27th July</date> last requested all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term>, regardless of their subjectship, to report to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police authorities</term>. Two days later, this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">decree</term> has been withdrawn. This is evidently a
				setback, which has given rise in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1072?dlid=deu" type="subject">public
					opinion</term> to various comments that are not worthy of being repeated, and at the same time leaves the question unaltered and,
				as before, heading for a solution that neither <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-767" type="subject"
					>diocesan authorities</term> nor others are able to oppose.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_raimondo_giustiniani">Giustiniani</persName></p>
